Yeah. He seems to be getting
a little more mature and smart.

20:04.975 --> 20:07.442
Yeah, Sue's getting kind of smart, too.

20:07.544 --> 20:09.410
It's weird.

20:10.247 --> 20:11.674
It's like...

20:12.549 --> 20:15.950
...they've been
watching us their whole life,

20:16.052 --> 20:18.686
and now they know stuff about us.

20:18.789 --> 20:21.222
Did you remember to pick up
soap the other day?

20:21.324 --> 20:23.674
Uh, no, I forgot.

20:24.494 --> 20:25.760
I'm sorry.

20:27.097 --> 20:29.049
Did you just say, "I'm sorry"?

20:30.066 --> 20:32.534
Yeah. What's the big deal?

20:32.636 --> 20:34.936
You never say you're sorry.

20:35.038 --> 20:36.037
Okay.

20:36.139 --> 20:37.505
Don't make a big drama out of it.

20:37.574 --> 20:39.496
I'm not making a...

20:40.811 --> 20:42.477
You're right.

20:42.579 --> 20:44.112
I'm gonna work on that.

20:47.717 --> 20:48.716
You know, you think you need to

20:48.785 --> 20:50.685
role model for your kids,

20:50.787 --> 20:52.053
but the fact is

20:52.155 --> 20:53.955
whether you think
you're modeling or not,

20:54.057 --> 20:56.157
they are watching you.

20:56.226 --> 20:59.294
They've been watching you
the whole time.

20:59.396 --> 21:02.130
Okay, Axl and I threw out
everything that's ruined.

21:02.232 --> 21:04.215
All the rest of it
is just kind of ruined,

21:04.317 --> 21:06.568
so I'm guessing we're keeping it.

21:06.670 --> 21:09.103
How is it that my Lily Tomlin
"And That's the Truth" album

21:09.206 --> 21:12.240
gets wrecked and that box of old
answering machines is dry as a bone?

21:12.342 --> 21:13.608
I don't know.

21:19.549 --> 21:22.617
We may not be perfect,
but we did a few things right.

21:22.719 --> 21:24.786
I mean, I think we did.

21:24.888 --> 21:26.688
I don't know. I'll ask the kids.

